                <h4>Secondary Science and Technology (54 credits)</h4>

    
              <p>54 credits in designated science courses selected to provide subject matter expertise in the four areas of:<br />
the Material World<br />
- Earth and Space<br />
- the Living World<br />
- the Technological World</p>
<p>All students need to plan their course selections with attention to the prerequisites.</p>
    
      
      
                <h4>Required Courses (15 credits)</h4>

    
              <p>3 credits of Statistics:</p>
    
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/math-203" class="program-course-title">
              MATH 203 Principles of Statistics 1 (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-29428" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
